Zambia’s Kaunda, 87, Hospitalized for Almost Week in Namibia, Times Says

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-08-16T08:25:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/zambia-s-kaunda-87-hospitalized-for-almost-week-in-namibia-times-says.html
Zambia’s first post-independence
leader, Kenneth Kaunda, 87, has been hospitalized for almost a
week in  Namibia ’s capital, Windhoek, the Times of Zambia
reported, citing Peter Mwaba, permanent secretary in the Health
Ministry.  Zambia’s government has dispatched a team of medical
specialists to Windhoek to assess Kaunda’s health, the Lusaka-
based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita in Lusaka via Johannesburg on 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
